data.name: Garchomp
data.flavorText: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

data.name: Manaphy
data.flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

data.name: Raichu
data.flavorText: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

data.name: Regigigas
data.flavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

data.name: Rotom
data.flavorText: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

data.name: Buizel
data.flavorText: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

data.name: Croagunk
data.flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.

data.name: Gabite
data.flavorText: It habitually digs up and hoards gems in its nest. Its loot is constantly targeted by thieves.

data.name: Lopunny
data.flavorText: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.

data.name: Pachirisu
data.flavorText: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It live atop trees.

data.name: Pichu
data.flavorText: It plays with others by touching tails and setting off sparks. This appears to be a test of courage.

data.name: Buneary
data.flavorText: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

data.name: Chimchar
data.flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.

data.name: Gible
data.flavorText: Its nests is small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.

data.name: Piplup
data.flavorText: It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.

data.name: Turtwig
data.flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.
